title: For Sale:  Saiga 12 - Converted and Ready to Rock N Roll!
postcontent:
Saiga 12 - Converted and ready to "Rock N Roll!" - $1650

This converted Saiga 12 has just what you need -  a 20 round drum magazine,  rail mounted red dot optics, pressure actuated front end laser, Tri-rail foregrip, 19" barrel, and a folding stock. I like to call it "Mr. Destructo". 

I haven't shot it a lot, but when I do it leaves you realizing that it's ONE POWERFUL WEAPON, and a lot of fun to shoot!  To see this shotgun in action go to YouTube and enter "Saiga 12 Pallets" and watch this baby do it's thing. I laugh everytime I watch that video.

If you don't know about a Saiga 12, basically it's an AK47 shotgun. This 12 Gauge Combat Shotgun, made in Russia by Izhmash, is from the same company that produces the Kalashinikov series of assualt riflles - the original AK47's. Looking at the Saiga 12, you might even think that it's an AK.

To get the most out of your Saiga 12, you convert them by moving a new improved trigger assembly and firing components forward to where the trigger was originally designed to be by Kalashinikov . They come to the US with the forward trigger hole already cut out ready for conversion so no new cutting of metal is required, only changing out parts to bring them into 922r compliance so that you can legally attach the 20 round drum mag setup in its original AK configuration - that's when the fun starts! With all that said, the result is that this gun is 922r compliant and legal, and ready to Rock N' Roll. 

Now that you have read all that, have you watched the video yet? It's the clencher that makes you say "Hmmmm, he's right, I should have one of those around the house".

Gun features  - 
Tactical Aluminum Tri-rail Foregrip w/ Optional Rubber Covers

Tapco Piston
Original stock and foregrip

With all the talk about weapon bans, I am almost certain that this gun will be one of the top guns to make the upcoming ban list! I'm sure that Obama and Feinstein would love to see this one off the market!  But for now, it's still available and this is your chance to get one. 

I hope you enjoyed the video, it always makes me smile............. in an evil sort of way.
